  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Mosquito bites commonly result in redness, swelling and itching. This study will determine if
      a device that emits a small piezo-electrical impulse can provide relief from these symptoms.
      Volunteers entering the study will have a mosquito bite on one forearm. Redness and
      irritation will be recorded periodically for 24 hours. Comparing data from subjects
      randomised to the treatment or a placebo device will be analysed to determine effectiveness
      of the product. We will also ask the subjects their view on how easy the product is to use
      and clarity of instructions provided.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
